\pard\pardeftab720\sa120
\cf0 where
\i  dp
\i0  is the change in the psychological experience,
\i  k
\i0  is a constant to be determined experimentally,
\i  dS
\i0  is the change in the stimulus and
\i  S
\i0  is the stimulus. He added to this the idea that the physical stimulus must break a certain threshold to be perceivable at all to derive what is now known as 'Fechner's law':\
